Work Group:     Core
Issue Number:   507
Title:          Must a temporary initializing an object be destroyed _as soon 
                as_ it has been copied?
Section:        12.2 [class.temporary]
Status:         active
Description:
	12.2p4 says:
	"The object is initialized from a copy of the temporary; during this
	 copying, an implementation can call the copy constructor many times;	
	 the temporary is destroyed as soon as it has been copied."
	
	Bill says:   
	don't recall the requirement of "as soon as it has been copied";
        I thought it was any time before the end of the initialization.
Resolution:
	Proposal:
	Change the sentence above to:
	"... the temporary shall be destroyed after it has been copied, before 
	 or when the initialization completes."
